      <p><b>Synopsis</b>:</p>
      <p>Neural networks and deep learning often provide impressive solutions to
        many problems in image analysis, speech recognition, language processing
        and etc. They are part of a broader family of statistical learning
        methods based on learning representations of data.&nbsp; In
        particular,&nbsp; the “Deep Learning” systems, typified by deep neural
        networks, are increasingly taking over all AI tasks, ranging from
        language understanding, and speech and image recognition, to machine
        translation, planning, and even game playing and autonomous driving. As
        a result, expertise in deep learning is fast changing from an esoteric
        desirable to a mandatory prerequisite in many advanced academic
        settings, and a large advantage in the industrial job market. The goal
        of deep learning is to replace hand-crafted features with efficient
        algorithms for unsupervised or semi-supervised feature learning and
        hierarchical feature extraction. This course covers the core methods,
        concepts and algorithms in neural networks and deep learning.</p>
